Raj Rajaratnam’s Arrest Led Brother Rengan to Take Notebooks, Smith Claims

-- B y   D a v i d   G l o v i n ,   B o b   V a n   V o r i s   a n d   P a t r i c i a   H u r t a d o
-- 
2011-03-28T13:55:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/raj-rajaratnam-s-arrest-led-brother-rengan-to-take-notebooks-smith-claims.html
Shortly after Raj Rajaratnam was
arrested Oct. 16, 2009, his brother Rengan went into the Galleon
Group LLC’s co-founder’s office and removed his sibling’s
private notebooks, according to court filings regarding
allegations made by ex-trader  Adam Smith , who may testify in the
Galleon insider trading case in  Manhattan  this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Glovin in New York at 
 dglovin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Rovella at 
 drovella@bloomberg.net  